# MkDocs MobileWheels Plugin

A MkDocs plugin that adds Python package compatibility search functionality to your documentation site using a WASM-powered SQLite database.

## Features

- üîç **Fast Search**: Search through 750k+ Python packages instantly
- üì± **Mobile Support**: Check iOS and Android compatibility
- üìã **Requirements Analysis**: Upload requirements.txt to analyze all dependencies
- ‚ö° **Client-Side**: No backend required - runs entirely in the browser
- üéØ **Easy Integration**: Just add to your mkdocs.yml plugins

## Installation

### From GitHub (Recommended for now)

```bash
pip install git+https://github.com/Py-Swift/MobileWheelsDatabase.git
```

### From PyPI (Coming Soon)

```bash
pip install mkdocs-mobilewheels
```

## Usage

### Basic Configuration

Add the plugin to your `mkdocs.yml`:

```yaml
plugins:
  - mobilewheels
```

This will automatically add a "Package Search" page to your site at `/package-search/`.

### Advanced Configuration

```yaml
plugins:
  - mobilewheels:
      page_path: "packages"              # Custom URL path (default: package-search)
      page_title: "Find Packages"        # Custom page title
      database_url: "https://cdn.example.com/db"  # Custom database location
      include_in_nav: true               # Include in navigation (default: true)
```

### Creating the Search Page

Create a markdown file at `docs/package-search.md` (or your custom path):

```markdown
# Python Package Compatibility Search

Search for Python packages and check their iOS/Android compatibility.

<!-- The plugin will inject the search interface here -->
```

## How It Works

The plugin:

1. **Copies Assets**: Automatically copies the WASM binary and SQLite databases to your site
2. **Injects Interface**: Adds the search UI to your designated page
3. **Client-Side Search**: All searching happens in the browser using WebAssembly

## Database Structure

- **index-1.sqlite, index-2.sqlite**: Package name indexes
- **data-1.sqlite through data-29.sqlite**: Package metadata (25k packages each)
- **MobileWheelsDatabase.wasm**: Swift WASM binary for querying (~59MB)

## Configuration Options

| Option | Type | Default | Description |
|--------|------|---------|-------------|
| `page_path` | string | `package-search` | URL path for the search page |
| `page_title` | string | `Python Package Compatibility Search` | Page title |
| `database_url` | string | `/mobilewheels_assets` | Base URL for database files |
| `include_in_nav` | boolean | `true` | Include page in navigation |

## Hosting the Database

By default, the plugin copies all database files to your site. For large deployments, you can host the database files on a CDN:

```yaml
plugins:
  - mobilewheels:
      database_url: "https://cdn.example.com/mobilewheels"
```

Upload these files to your CDN:
- `MobileWheelsDatabase.wasm`
- `index-1.sqlite`, `index-2.sqlite`
- `data-1.sqlite` through `data-29.sqlite`
- `package-search.js`

